<item>
            <title>[HIVE-6392] Hive (and HCatalog) don&apos;t allow super-users to add partitions to tables.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-6392</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HDFS allows for users to be added to a &quot;supergroup&quot; (identified by the &quot;dfs.permissions.superusergroup&quot; key in hdfs-site.xml). Users in this group are allowed to modify HDFS contents regardless of the path&apos;s ogw permissions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, Hive&apos;s StorageBasedAuthProvider disallows such a superuser from adding partitions to any table that doesn&apos;t explicitly grant write permissions to said superuser. This causes the odd scenario where the superuser writes data to a partition-directory (under the table&apos;s path), but can&apos;t register the appropriate partition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch that brings the Metastore&apos;s behaviour in line with what the HDFS allows.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
